README.md

Services Engineering Reading List

   A reading list for services engineering, with a focus on cloud
   infrastructure services.

   We welcome
   suggestions.

Papers

     * [http://queue.acm.org/detail.cfm?id=2353017]Fault Injection in
       Production (Allspaw)
     * [http://www.erlang.org/download/armstrong_thesis_2003.pdf]Making
       Reliable Distributed Systems in the Presence of Software Errors
       (Armstrong)
     * [http://www.bailis.org/papers/hat-vldb2014.pdf]Highly Available
       Transactions: Virtues and Limitations (Bailis et al.)
     * [http://www.high-reliability.org/files/The_Incident_Command_System.
       pdf]The Incident Command System (Bigley and Roberts)
     * [http://static.googleusercontent.com/external_content/untrusted_dlc
       p/research.google.com/en/us/archive/chubby-osdi06.pdf]The Chubby
       Lock Service for Loosely Coupled Distributed Systems (Burrows)
     * [http://www.read.seas.harvard.edu/%7Ekohler/class/cs239-w08/chang06
       bigtable.pdf]Bigtable: a Distributed Storage System for Structured
       Data (Chang et al.)
     * [http://research.google.com/archive/spanner-osdi2012.pdf]Spanner:
       Google's Globally-Distributed Database (Corbett et al.)
     * [http://www.read.seas.harvard.edu/%7Ekohler/class/cs239-w08/decandi
       a07dynamo.pdf]Dynamo: Amazon's Highly Available Key-Value Store
       (DeCandia et al.)
     * [http://research.google.com/archive/mapreduce-osdi04.pdf]MapReduce:
       Simplified Data Processing on Large Clusters (Dean and Ghemawat)
     * [http://research.google.com/archive/gfs-sosp2003.pdf]The Google
       File System (Ghemawat et al.)
     * [http://mvdirona.com/jrh/talksAndPapers/JamesRH_Lisa.pdf]On
       Designing and Deploying Internet Scale Services (Hamilton)
     * [http://research.microsoft.com/en-us/UM/people/srikanth/netdb11/net
       db11papers/netdb11-final12.pdf]Kafka: A Distributed Messaging
       System for Log Processing (Kreps et al.)
     * [http://queue.acm.org/detail.cfm?id=2371516]Weathering the
       Unexpected (Krishnan)
     * [http://vldb.org/pvldb/vol5/p1771_georgelee_vldb2012.pdf]The
       Unified Logging Infrastructure for Data Analytics at Twitter (Lee
       et al.)
     * [http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.222.1862&
       rep=rep1&type=pdf]Automatic Management of Partitioned, Replicated
       Search Services (Leibert et al.)
     * [http://best.dtu.dk/SC13/p20-casestudy.pdf]Learning to Embrace
       Failure (Limoncelli et al.)
     * [http://www.kdd.org/sites/default/files/issues/14-2-2012-12/V14-02-
       02-Lin.pdf]Scaling Big Data Mining Infrastructure: The Twitter
       Experience (Lin and Rayboy)
     * [http://static.googleusercontent.com/external_content/untrusted_dlc
       p/research.google.com/en/us/pubs/archive/36632.pdf]Dremel:
       Interactive Analysis of Web-Scale Datasets (Melnik et al.)
     * [http://shaffner.us/cs/papers/tarpit.pdf]Out of the Tar Pit
       (Moseley and Marks)
     * [http://www.cs.umb.edu/%7Eponeil/lsmtree.pdf]The Log-Structured
       Merge-Tree (O'Neil et al.)
     * [https://ramcloud.stanford.edu/wiki/download/attachments/11370504/r
       aft.pdf]In Search of an Understandable Consensus Algorithm (Ongaro
       and Ousterhout)
     * [http://static.googleusercontent.com/external_content/untrusted_dlc
       p/research.google.com/en/us/archive/disk_failures.pdf]Failure
       Trends in a Large Disk Drive Population (Pinheiro et al.)
     * [http://www.rgoarchitects.com/Files/fallacies.pdf]Fallacies of
       Distributed Computing Explained (Rotem-Gal-Oz)
     * [http://research.google.com/pubs/archive/38125.pdf]F1 - The
       Fault-Tolerant Distributed RDBMS Supporting Google's Ad Business
       (Shute et al.)
     * [http://research.google.com/pubs/archive/36356.pdf]Dapper, A Large
       Scale Distributed Systems Tracing Infrastructure (Sigelman et al.)
     * [https://www.usenix.org/system/files/conference/nsdi12/nsdi12-final
       138.pdf]Resident Distributed Datasets: a Fault-Tolerant Abstraction
       for In-Memory Cluster Computing (Zahari et al.)
     * [https://docs.google.com/file/d/0Byl4UKRYLErDVlJMNDNjaThiR2M/edit]T
       he Human Side of Postmortems (Zwieback)
     * [http://www.iaff.org/06news/NearMissKit/6.%20Crew%20Resource%20Mana
       gement/CRM.pdf]Crew Resource Management: a Positive Change for the
       Fire Service

Posts

     * [http://www.kitchensoap.com/2011/04/07/resilience-engineering-part-
       i/]Resilience Engineering: Part I,
       [http://www.kitchensoap.com/2012/06/18/resilience-engineering-part-
       ii-lenses/]Part II (Allspaw)
     * [http://www.kitchensoap.com/2011/07/18/systems-engineering-great-de
       finition/]Systems Engineering: a Great Definition (Allspaw)
     * [http://techblog.netflix.com/2012/07/chaos-monkey-released-into-wil
       d.html]Chaos Monkey Released Into The Wild (Bennett and Tseitlin)
     * [http://blog.b3k.us/2012/01/24/some-rules.html]Some Rules for
       Engineering and Operations (Black)
     * [http://blog.b3k.us/2009/07/15/service-level-disagreements.html]Ser
       vice Level Disagreements Part I,
       [http://blog.b3k.us/2009/07/16/service-level-disagreements-2.html]P
       art II (Black)
     * [http://yellerapp.com/posts/2015-03-16-incuriosity-killed-the-infra
       structure.html]Incuriosity Will Kill Your Infrastructure (Crayford)
     * [https://docs.google.com/document/d/199PqyG3UsyXlwieHaqbGiWVa8eMWi8
       zzAn0YfcApr8Q/edit#heading=h.whsaboyw21nk]My Philosophy on Alerting
       (Ewaschuk)
     * [http://codahale.com/you-cant-sacrifice-partition-tolerance/]You
       Can't Sacrifice Partition Tolerance (Hale)
     * [http://perspectives.mvdirona.com/2013/01/15/CustomerTrust.aspx]Cus
       tomer Trust (Hamilton)
     * [http://perspectives.mvdirona.com/2012/02/26/ObservationsOnErrorsCo
       rrectionsTrustOfDependentSystems.aspx]Observations on Errors,
       Corrections, & Trust of Dependent Systems (Hamilton)
     * [https://stripe.com/blog/game-day-exercises-at-stripe]Game Day
       Exercises at Stripe: Learning from kill -9 (Hedlund)
     * [http://cs.brown.edu/courses/cs227/archives/2012/papers/weaker/cidr
       07p15.pdf]Life Beyond Distributed Transactions: An Apostate's
       Opinion (Helland)
     * [http://www.somethingsimilar.com/2013/01/14/notes-on-distributed-sy
       stems-for-young-bloods/]Notes on Distributed Systems for Young
       Bloods (Hodges)
     * [http://aphyr.com/posts/288-the-network-is-reliable]The Network is
       Reliable (Kingsbury)
     * [http://aphyr.com/posts/299-the-trouble-with-timestamps]The Trouble
       with Clocks (Kingsbury)
     * [http://aphyr.com/posts/286-call-me-maybe-final-thoughts]Call Me
       Maybe: Final Thoughts (Kingsbury)
     * [http://blog.empathybox.com/post/19574936361/getting-real-about-dis
       tributed-system-reliability]Getting Real About Distributed Systems
       Reliability (Kreps)
     * [http://engineering.linkedin.com/distributed-systems/log-what-every
       -software-engineer-should-know-about-real-time-datas-unifying]The
       Log: What every software engineer should know about real-time
       data's unifying abstraction (Kreps)
     * [https://blog.heroku.com/archives/2014/5/9/incident-response-at-her
       oku]Incident Response at Heroku (McGranaghan)
     * [http://www.mnot.net/blog/2011/05/18/http_benchmark_rules]On HTTP
       Load Testing (Nottingham)
     * [https://blog.twitter.com/2013/observability-at-twitter]Observabili
       ty at Twitter (Watson)
     * [https://plus.google.com/112678702228711889851/posts/eVeouesvaVX]St
       evey's Google Platforms Rant (Yegge)

Presentations

     * [http://www.cs.cornell.edu/projects/ladis2009/talks/dean-keynote-la
       dis2009.pdf]Design, Lessons, and Advice from Building Distributed
       Systems at Google (Dean)
     * [http://www.mvdirona.com/jrh/TalksAndPapers/JamesHamilton_POA200902
       26.pdf]Service Design Best Practices (Hamilton)

Books

     * [http://www.amazon.com/Field-Guide-Understanding-Human-Error/dp/075
       4648265]The Field Guide To Understanding Human Error (Dekker)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/Agile-Retrospectives-Making-Teams-Great/dp/0
       977616649]Agile Retrospectives: Making Good Teams Great (Derby et
       al.)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0312427654]Better: A Surgeon's Notes on
       Performance (Gawande)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/The-Checklist-Manifesto-ebook/dp/B0030V0PEW]
       The Checklist Manifesto: How to Get Things Right (Gawande)
     * [http://chimera.labs.oreilly.com/books/1230000000545/index.html]Hig
       h Performance Browser Networking (Grigorik)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/Resilience-Engineering-Practice-Ashgate-Stud
       ies/dp/1409410358/]Resilience Engineering in Practice (Hollnagel et
       al.)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/Effective-Monitoring-Alerting-For-Operations
       /dp/1449333524]Effective Monitoring and Alerting (Ligus)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/Release-It-Production-Ready-Pragmatic-Progra
       mmers/dp/0978739213]Release It!: Design and Deploy Production-Ready
       Software (Nygard)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/The-Challenger-Launch-Decision-Technology/dp
       /0226851761]The Challenger Launch Decision (Vaughan)
     * [http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004IK9U4U]Managing the
       Unexpected (Weick and Sutcliffe)

